The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | NZ likely to replace Pak
                                                   NZ likely to replace Pak
                      
	New Delhi: New Zealand are likely to replace Pakistan in the four-nation Punjab Gold Cup hockey tournament, former Olympian and director of Punjab sports department Pargat Singh said.         
	The tournament will be held in Chandigarh and Jalandhar from January 31.         
	Meanwhile, Pakistan Hockey Federation (PHF) Thursday said that although it is keen to send the national team to India for a four-nation tournament later this month, a final decision would be taken by the foreign ministry. (PTI)                                                                                                                       
